<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870512-0089 </DOCNO><HL> Who's News:Philip Morris NamesSeveral Legal Officers</HL><DD> 05/12/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> WNEWS MO </IN><DATELINE> NEW YORK  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Philip Morris Cos. announced several changes in its legal department.    Murray H. Bring, a partner in a Washington law firm, was named to succeed Thomas F. Ahrensfeld as senior vice president and general counsel upon Mr. Ahrensfeld's retirement next year.    Donald Fried, a partner in a New York law firm, was named to succeed Eugene J.T. Flanagan as vice president, secretary, and associate general counsel upon Mr. Flanagan's retirement next year.    Alexander Holtzman, currently vice president and general counsel of Philip Morris U.S.A., was named vice president and associate general counsel of the parent, a tobacco and food company. Fredric S. Newman, assistant general counsel at the domestic unit, was named to succeed Mr. Holtzman. </TEXT></DOC>